snippet.textDisplay: That Back to the Future one isn't predicting hands-free gaming. It's referencing Duck Hunt/Light gun gaming. Something that ALREADY existed in the early 80s. In fact all this stuff is just reference to stuff that existed in some form, or was a variation on something that existed. The only exceptions I'll give are the Cubs (but even then that's just writing an absurdity for the sake of humour), and The Jetstons (but even then, that's when colour TV became a thing so I imagine it was just people thinking "it'd be cool if we could talk through our tvs").

Not believing flying cars will ever happen is possibly why it never did. They're HUGE safety concerns relating to flying cars anyway. Planes can be easily handled. Planes fly way up. Flying cars would have to be MUCH lower to the ground...and closer to buildings. Think about the possible air traffic.. For flying cars to be less of a hazard, people would have to live in the skies to.
I don't see flying cars being cleared for use amongst pedestrians any time soon, but yeah. Flying cars did and do exist (for a while now).
It's the safety measures and general necessities in the way of public use. [Planes, jets and helicopters already do great enough jobs and have size and landing control..but things aren't in place to have both those things for flying cars yet. Before something is ever released to the public, it has to be both efficient and safe.
Depending on how civilisation goes, flying cars might never be a thing. Spacecraft, but not flying cars.
